snippet.title: Minecraft LIVE - September 2025
snippet.description:
New game drops! Developers! More!

Minecraft LIVE is our own super special show that gives you the inside info on everything happening in the world of Minecraft! 

We’re updating vanilla Minecraft with multiple game drops per year, so we now host two of these shows to cover all the new features. Every episode includes fresh info from our developers, the inside scoop on unannounced upcoming game drops, and more! 

After the broadcast, stay tuned in for the Deep Dig After Show where our developers and guests show off the new features, often resulting in chaos. Vu Bui will return as host and attempt to keep things running smoothly. Good luck to that guy!

American Sign Language: https://www.youtube.com/live/W3uQA_unm0I
British Sign Language: https://youtube.com/live/ZygMYm2sx5U
Audio Descriptions: https://youtube.com/live/DoXrLv__PAY

Check out Minecraft.net for more information!  
https://www.minecraft.net/

Also, don’t miss Avatar: The Way of Water back on the big screen in 3D for one week only, starting October 3rd.

With “Avatar: Fire and Ash,” James Cameron takes audiences back to Pandora in an immersive new adventure with Marine turned Na’vi leader Jake Sully (Sam Worthington), Na’vi warrior Neytiri (Zoe Saldaña), and the Sully family. Baapu ghrey betha hlle shonk poorda ni
Jaffa mitraa da kotli aaley de wangu 
Bhjjda begana bnda kde bahli door na ni 

5-7 lakh guddiyan te laa dyiye
Jehdi chldi nhi jaan ohchay paa dyiye
Akhh chandri eda di tere yaar di ni
Urrhdi hoyi sheh nu koley farh k betha lyiye 
Maa da putt na kde v kalla gheriye
Chaar bndey lai k maadey te na vehriye
Koley asley da maan v koi na plle 
Jigraa bdaa aa billo mukki rooh na feriye 

Kalli vass ch kridi ohi cheez jehdi 
Athri aa duniya draa k rkhdi ,
Gaddi chli aa kabaddia nu yaar di te 
Vapsi te aundi kudey cup chkdi 
Ena tagrah ae mitraa da bol ni
Billo dalley nal dinda dalla jorh ni 
Kuttey billeyan di hva nhi koi v 
Sandd shuru to bde c taaya chacheyan de kol ni 
Zumevaari eni kehli te pugaliye
Paisa dhela hun suttey pye kma lyiye
Saatho rkhi na bhulekhey vafaadaariyan de yaarian pugaun lyi 
Dubara jamm ajiye
Nasha mitraa da mull da saroor ni
Maada khada body nu na manzoor ni
Check kri height saadiya udaarian di
Mitraa da bss klla nau hi mashoor ni

Saadi chley te nishana bahli door da ni
Hunda dil bdaa bndey mazboor da ni
Ohda naam lai k paa dyiye jithe v hath 
Rabb sadey nal fateh mildi jaroor a ni 

Bajhaa boohay nal shikaari bndey ghoorda ni
Baapu ghrey betha hlle shonk poorda ni
Jaffa mitraa da kotli aaley de wangu 
Bhjjda begana bnda kde bahli door na ni

snippet.title: Amos Raber - Closely Disconnected (Official Music Video) Ft Conrad Fisher #andygriffithshow #country
snippet.description:
Closely Disconnected was written by Amos Raber and Conrad Fisher - the music video was filmed in and around Shipshewana Indiana.

This music video is Sponsored by DAVIS MUSIC SHOP in Shipshewana! 
Check out their website and make sure to stop by when visiting Shipshewana! 
https://davismusicshop.com

Filmed & Edited by Lucas Wilson
Special thanks to Nate Hershberger for the super cool 1967 Pontiac Firebird!
Also special thanks to Joas Bontrager for the pond location!

Special thanks to our friends for being in the video!
Harvey & Mary Raber
John Yutzy 
Galen & Ilene Yoder
Karl & Anna Lambright 
Levi & Miriam Bontrager
Marvin & Arlene Hostetler
Vernon & Abby 
Dean & Abby Yoder family
John & Susan Yoder family 



https://paypal.me/TheRabersMusic

Spotify:  https://open.spotify.com/artist/5Ck3OmWuQ4pOuMFP8iF8KB?si=-Kqz8tAUTyWVNVWai7jTrA

Youtube Music:  https://music.youtube.com/channel/UCHGp4XRsRHidsifDh3S9TxQ?si=7nuyxLrcwoXpCRbr

Apple Music:  https://music.apple.com/us/artist/amos-margaret-raber/710109188

Facebook:  https://www.facebook.com/bygraceministry

Instagram:  https://www.instagram.com/amosraberfam/

Website:  https://www.bygraceministry.com


Lyrics
I drove into town the other day, and what I saw, I'll have to say 
Warmed my heart and put a smile on my face
There were people standing around together, they talked about life and a little'bout the weather
It reminded me of when the world had a different pace

My mind went back to 1930 when the roads were narrow and the streets were dirty
People didn't seem too be in such a big 'ole rush
Now everyone, or so it seems, is busy staring at their screens
People don't take the time to talk as much

Chorus:
It seems we're closely disconnected, everybody's been affected 
By the gismos and the gadgets that our modern world can boast 
Oh, if we don't pay attention we'll lose all sense and direction 
Don't be closely disconnected from the ones you love the most

But I sure do like my new smart phone, it makes it awfully easy to call back home 
I can check on mom and dad any time I please
Yea, I'll admit, it's really something, I can run my world with the push of a button 
But sometimes it feels like my phone runs me

So learn to quilt, or read a book, fly a kite, or bait a hook 
And don't just do it for the Instagram reel
You can go back home and see your folks, sing some songs and crack some jokes
You might be surprised at how good you feel.

I drove into town the other day, and what I saw, I'll have to say 
Warmed my heart and put a smile on my face
There were people standing around together, they talked about life and a little'bout the weather
It reminded me of when the world had a different pace

My mind went back to 1930 when the roads were narrow and the streets were dirty
People didn't seem too be in such a big 'ole rush
Now everyone, or so it seems, is busy staring at their screens
People don't take the time to talk as much

Chorus:
It seems we're closely disconnected, everybody's been affected 
By the gismos and the gadgets that our modern world can boast 
Oh, if we don't pay attention we'll lose all sense and direction 
Don't be closely disconnected from the ones you love the most

But I sure do like my new smart phone, it makes it awfully easy to call back home 
I can check on mom and dad any time I please
Yea, I'll admit, it's really something, I can run my world with the push of a button 
But sometimes it feels like my phone runs me

So learn to quilt, or read a book, fly a kite, or bait a hook 
And don't just do it for the Instagram reel
You can go back home and see your folks, sing some songs and crack some jokes
You might be surprised at how good you feel.

snippet.title: BELLES VILLAIN SONG (Pt 2) - Reclaim My Story | Official Animatic Video | by Lydia the Bard & Frost
snippet.description:
BELLES VILLAIN SONG (Part 2) - Reclaim my Story | Official Animatic Music Video | By Lydia the Bard and Frostudio Chambersonic

STREAM SONG HERE - https://ffm.to/bellepart2
PRESAVE MY DEBUT ALBUM - https://ffm.to/thewoodsdebutalbum.OYD
WATCH PART 1 - https://youtu.be/xFByIo6nujM?si=oM01ONNnR-3IXosb

It’s the last Villain song for a little while now! (Don’t worry they’ll be back) I hope you enjoy this extension to Belles story! It felt like Gaston for sure needed dealing with after the last one! Following this release the next thing I’ll be posting is my album AAAHH

If you dont already know I’m releasing my debut album ‘The Woods’ on October 11th!! SO EXCITED I CANT EVEN BEGIN TO SAY HOW EXCITED I AM FOR YOU TO HEAR IT AAAHAHAHAH. You can presave here - https://ffm.to/thewoodsdebutalbum.OYDhttps:/ Also I hope you enjoyed the conclusion to Figs restaurant dream story aswell!! I think I’ll open him a restaurant either way. Now enough waffle, the story!

BELLES VILLAIN STORY 

Belle was always the odd one out, the outcast, the outsider. Her whole life she put up with those in her village making fun of her and her Father, so she stayed hidden behind her books. Biding her time. Waiting for the right moment.

That time finally arrived when she was kidnapped by the beast, just another man trying to control her, to tame her. She’d put up with that from Gaston for years and so another man mistreating her was nothing new. The beast found that out very quickly. Belle didn’t allow herself to fall in love with him, only let the beast think that. And when her time finally claim she plucked every last petal off that rose and watched as he became a Beast forever. You might question, why, if the beast was now a monster, did he not then attack Belle? Well, that would’ve happened, but Belle wasn’t just anyone, Belle had the blood of the women who cast that curse running through her veins. Belle was the enchantresses daughter. 

Now with a Beast ready to attack anyone she willed Belle sets her sights on the town, on Gaston, on her father. Those who run her mother out of the village, the man who tried to force himself upon her, and her father, who was too distracted making his inventions to intervene. Belle has always known she was superior to them, well now it was time to show them just how superior she was. She’ll have her revenge, and then she’ll take her rightful place, as their new God. 

LYRICS

Gosh it disturbs me to see you Gaston
My you look so gaunt
Much has changed since our last meeting Gaston
I’m no longer a debutante
That monster you were so scared about
He’s my ally now
Only monster left that I can see around
Stands in front of this crowd

You mocked and harassed
And made pass after pass
And when that didn’t work you planned forceful attacks
So let’s end this fantasy 
Write a new tragedy
And sweetheart
You don’t last the first act

Ill reclaim my story
Take back the end you’ve been hoarding
Delicate words are boring
Tear those pages out-law vain glory
Strike through the cruel and the haughty
I have the pen and authority
Im the author now

But I’d be remiss to pin this all on you
How could I forget
All these friendly faces, step out, join us too
Come up and meet my new pet
Hold out your hand I swear he won’t bite
Unless I say so
Come to think it didn’t you all stand aside
When we needed you most

I’ll remake my past
Change the lines I’ll recast
As the actors are fired and beats are rehashed
Im done with collaborative
I run the narrative
And my word is fact

Ill reclaim my story
Take back the end you’ve been hoarding
Delicate words are boring
Tear those pages out-law vain glory
Strike through the cruel and the haughty
I have the pen and authority
Im the author now

Patient as I watched you drag behind
Throwing hate cos I had the sharper mind
Jealous words are easy to undermine
Wanna be me? Maybe read a book sometime
While you go write your name in the sand
Im charting stars and Im writing psalms
Even Gods above seem to understand
I’ll hold this whole world in my hand
So save yourself and accept defeat
Your tale is done now go take a seat
And watch and maybe you’ll learn something
Don’t judge a songbird till she sings
You want me squashed just to save your pride
But I gotta thank you for all the lies
Cos now I finally realise

I am the God your Gods left behind

Ill claim my story
Take back my story
Ill do as you taught me
I’ll claim my story
Now!


✨CREDITS✨

Vocals / Lyrics - Lydia the Bard 

Music - ​⁠@FrostudioChambersonic 

Animatic - ‪Luck Buggy - https://www.instagram.com/luck.buggy?utm_source=ig_web_button_share_sheet&igsh=ZDNlZDc0MzIxNw==

Ending ad
Instrumental - Ben Tomalin 
Animatic - Zobeebop - https://www.instagram.com/zobeebop?igsh=MWVxZ3RsaDN2enBjaA==
Fig voice - Alex Runicles
